# Set Up Authentication

## Arguments
- `service`: Service name to add auth to
- `type`: `jwt` | `s2s` | `both` (JWT for user auth, S2S for service-to-service)

## Architecture

```
Request → Bearer token → @ironplate/auth middleware → verify JWT → req.auth
                                                   ↓ fail
                                              401 Unauthorized
```

## Steps

### 1. Add Dependencies
- Add `@ironplate/auth` to `apps/{service}/package.json`
- Run `{{ .Project.Spec.Monorepo.PackageManager }} install`

### 2. Configure Auth Middleware

```typescript
import { createService } from '@ironplate/service';
import { createAuthMiddleware } from '@ironplate/auth';
import type { IPlugin, PluginContext } from '@ironplate/service';

const authPlugin: IPlugin = {
  name: 'auth',
  order: 30,
  async initialize(ctx: PluginContext) {
    const middleware = createAuthMiddleware({
      jwt: {
        secret: process.env.JWT_SECRET!,
        issuer: '{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}',
        audience: '{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}',
      },
      excludePaths: ['/healthz', '/readyz', '/metrics', ...ctx.getAuthExcludePaths()],
    });
    ctx.addMiddleware({ handler: middleware, order: 30 });
  },
};
```

### 3. Access Auth Context in Routes

```typescript
import type { AuthenticatedRequest } from '@ironplate/auth';
import { Router } from 'express';

const router = Router();

router.get('/me', (req, res) => {
  const authReq = req as AuthenticatedRequest;
  const userId = authReq.auth?.userId;
  // ...
});
```

### 4. Protect Specific Routes

```typescript
import { requireClaim, requireServiceAuth } from '@ironplate/auth';

// Require admin role
router.delete('/users/:id', requireClaim('role', 'admin'), deleteUser);

// Require service-to-service auth (internal APIs only)
router.post('/internal/sync', requireServiceAuth(), syncHandler);
```

### 5. Set Up Service-to-Service Auth

```typescript
import { ServiceTokenProvider } from '@ironplate/auth';
import { createHttpClient } from '@ironplate/http-client';

const tokenProvider = new ServiceTokenProvider({
  serviceName: '{service}',
  secret: process.env.S2S_SECRET!,
});

// Auto-attach S2S token to outbound requests
const internalClient = createHttpClient({
  baseURL: 'http://other-service:3000',
  headers: {
    Authorization: await tokenProvider.getAuthHeader(),
  },
});
```

### 6. Add Environment Variables
- Add to Helm `values.yaml`:
  ```yaml
  env:
    JWT_SECRET: "from-external-secrets"
    S2S_SECRET: "from-external-secrets"
  ```

## Token Types

| Type | Payload | Expiry | Use |
|------|---------|--------|-----|
| Access | `{ sub: userId }` | 15m | User API calls |
| Refresh | `{ sub: userId, type: 'refresh' }` | 7d | Token renewal |
| Service | `{ sub: 'service:name', type: 'service' }` | 1h (auto-refreshed) | S2S calls |

## CRITICAL Rules
- NEVER log JWT tokens — use structured logging with token metadata only
- NEVER store JWT secrets in code — always use environment variables / external secrets
- ALWAYS validate token expiry — the library does this automatically
- ALWAYS set `excludePaths` for health checks and metrics endpoints
- ALWAYS use `requireServiceAuth()` for internal-only endpoints
- Service tokens are auto-cached and refreshed 5 minutes before expiry

## Checklist
- [ ] `@ironplate/auth` dependency added
- [ ] Auth middleware registered as plugin with order 30
- [ ] Health/metrics paths excluded from auth
- [ ] Routes access `req.auth` for user context
- [ ] Sensitive routes use `requireClaim` or `requireServiceAuth`
- [ ] JWT_SECRET configured via external secrets
- [ ] S2S token provider set up for internal calls
